<h3 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h3>
<p>ince the product rule is what we use to differentiate a product, then perhaps its analog would be of use here.   The product rule for differentiation can be expressed as</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\dx(uv){}=u\dx{v}{}+v\dx{u}{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">Rearranging this a bit we have</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
u\dx{v}{}=\dx(uv){}-v\dx{u}.
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">or</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\int{}u\dx{v}{}=\int{} \left(\dx(uv){}-v\dx{u}{}\right) = \int\dx(uv){}-\int
v\dx{u}{=uv-\int v\dx{u}{}}.
\end{equation*}
</div>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-5.html#p-95" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
</body>
